Metatibia much larger than mesotibia (as in 
Fig. 20
). Elytron at humerus with minute denticle. Male: TA of aedeagus (
Figs 87, 89
) with long flagellum; sclerite­complex at base of flagellum in repose at angle (45°–90°) with apodeme of aedeagus. Apical scoop of pedon at apex with median extension (
Fig. 160
). Tergite VIII apically with distinct notch. Female: Setose patch of venter consisting of 3 single rows of modified setae. Tergite VIII with sides converging towards concave apex. Length of ductus spermathecae plus spermatheca 3.8–4.3 X as long as tergite VIII.
